WEBVTT

00:57.724 --> 00:59.059
[indistinct chatter]

01:01.853 --> 01:03.897
[Aunt 1] Yeah, she'd like that, I'm sure.

01:03.981 --> 01:05.107
[Aunt 2] Can you imagine?

01:05.190 --> 01:07.192
[Aunt 1] [sighs] Such a good daughter!

01:07.484 --> 01:10.404
I mean, the poor thing's been taking care
of her for years.

01:10.904 --> 01:12.364
What she sacrificed.

01:12.698 --> 01:14.157
[screams]

01:14.241 --> 01:16.493
[Aunt 2]
At least now she will be free to go back.

01:19.746 --> 01:22.833
[Aunt 1] Can she ever really
perform again? It's been a decade.

01:22.916 --> 01:24.918
Well, what else is she gonna do?

01:25.002 --> 01:28.338
Uh, I don't know.
I don't think she even knows.

02:15.636 --> 02:16.678
[Charlotte] <i>Anton,</i>

02:17.012 --> 02:17.846
<i>Paloma,</i>

02:18.472 --> 02:19.973
<i>it's Charlotte Willmore.</i>

02:20.807 --> 02:21.725
[clears throat]

02:23.143 --> 02:23.977
<i>Anton,</i>

02:24.603 --> 02:25.479
<i>Paloma...</i>

02:27.814 --> 02:28.774
<i>Anton,</i>

02:28.857 --> 02:31.193
<i>Paloma, it's Charlotte Willmore.</i>

02:31.276 --> 02:33.487
<i>Yes, it's me. Hi.</i>

02:35.989 --> 02:37.074
[voicemail beeps]

02:37.574 --> 02:39.284
<i>Anton, Paloma. Hi.</i>

02:39.368 --> 02:41.787
<i>It's Charlotte Willmore.</i>

02:41.870 --> 02:44.206
<i>I don't know where you are in the world.</i>

02:44.289 --> 02:47.292
<i>Scouting young cellists</i>
<i>somewhere exotic, I'm sure.</i>

02:48.001 --> 02:53.048
<i>Anyway, um, I know it's been forever,</i>
<i>but my mother finally passed away</i>

02:53.131 --> 02:55.300
<i>and I'm not needed here anymore.</i>

02:55.384 --> 02:56.385
<i>So...</i>

02:56.468 --> 02:57.386
<i>if it's okay,</i>

02:57.469 --> 02:59.513
<i>I'd like to come and join you.</i>

03:40.762 --> 03:42.347
[music playing]

04:04.161 --> 04:05.162
[Anton] Charlotte.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.604
Paloma and I are so sorry
about your mother.

04:34.483 --> 04:37.360
[Anton] After a five-month search
over three continents,

04:37.444 --> 04:39.154
we are thrilled to bring our

04:39.237 --> 04:44.409
remarkable finalists together
in Shanghai for one last concert.

04:44.826 --> 04:46.995
The Bachoff Academy in Boston,

04:47.704 --> 04:50.707
founded by my grandfather Emil in 1927,

04:50.791 --> 04:53.668
is quite frankly the premiere 
private music facility

04:53.752 --> 04:56.046
for young cellists in the world.

04:56.129 --> 04:59.382
And each year, we teach hundreds
of day students in Massachusetts,

04:59.466 --> 05:02.677
but only a select handful
are given the opportunity

05:02.761 --> 05:06.264
privilege, really,
to reside and study at the Academy,

05:06.348 --> 05:09.434
which is why I'm so excited
that the winner tonight will receive

05:09.518 --> 05:12.729
a four-year live-in scholarship
to Bachoff.

05:12.813 --> 05:14.356
[audience applause]

05:18.193 --> 05:20.237
Now, the fact

05:20.320 --> 05:23.323
that my most prized protégé,

05:23.406 --> 05:27.327
Elizabeth Wells, one of the best
young cellists on the planet,

05:27.953 --> 05:30.872
will be judging tonight's final concert
is testament

05:31.289 --> 05:34.000
to just how talented
these three young ladies are.

05:35.669 --> 05:39.422
Listening to Lizzie play music so...
pure, so perfect

05:39.506 --> 05:42.634
is as close to God as you can get.

05:42.717 --> 05:45.136
Well, it's as close to God
as I want to get for the time being.

05:45.220 --> 05:46.972
-[audience laugh]
-[Anton] Uh...

05:47.055 --> 05:49.766
But Lizzie's not the only surprise we have
for you this evening.

05:49.850 --> 05:51.935
For four glorious years,

05:52.644 --> 05:55.480
I trained Charlotte Willmore at Bachoff.

05:55.856 --> 05:57.649
Charlotte was a rare and gifted talent

05:57.732 --> 06:02.153
poised for the type of greatness
achieved by very few,

06:02.237 --> 06:03.738
but then as all of you know,

06:04.197 --> 06:05.866
Charlotte's beloved mother, Ruth,

06:06.575 --> 06:07.492
got sick.

06:08.910 --> 06:13.373
Charlotte put her career on hold,
and went back home care for her mother.

06:13.957 --> 06:15.792
This is the heart of Charlotte.

06:25.677 --> 06:26.845
[machine whirs]

06:28.555 --> 06:32.309
I was thrilled that Charlotte reached out
to Paloma and myself,

06:32.934 --> 06:34.978
thrilled that after nearly a decade,

06:35.061 --> 06:36.271
she's back in our lives.

06:36.354 --> 06:39.649
Ladies and gentlemen,
our second judge for this evening,

06:39.733 --> 06:41.026
Charlotte Willmore.

06:51.036 --> 06:52.579
[boat horn blares]

06:55.749 --> 06:57.459
[Paloma]
It's baijiu. Chinese vodka.

06:57.542 --> 06:59.377
Two shots will have you
fluent in Mandarin.

06:59.461 --> 07:00.921
[laughs] Charlotte!

07:01.588 --> 07:02.964
Good, I was looking for you.

07:03.048 --> 07:05.884
You must remember these two
grueling taskmasters from the Academy?

07:05.967 --> 07:08.970
Oh, my goodness.
It's so wonderful to see you.

07:09.429 --> 07:10.597
Theis and Geoffrey.

07:10.680 --> 07:12.641
And after all these years! Mm.

07:13.516 --> 07:14.851
Charlotte, there you are!

07:16.102 --> 07:17.103
Would you excuse us?

07:17.854 --> 07:20.440
I want to introduce you,
before we have to go upstairs and start.

07:20.523 --> 07:22.192
She's so excited to meet you.

07:24.152 --> 07:27.280
And here she is, Charlotte, my star.

07:27.864 --> 07:29.240
-Elizabeth--
-Elizabeth Wells.

07:29.324 --> 07:30.450
Of course.

07:31.910 --> 07:33.203
Lizzie, please.

07:34.204 --> 07:35.163
Hey.

07:37.040 --> 07:40.210
Your music, Lizzie,
it's something more than beautiful.

07:42.337 --> 07:43.630
[Anton] I mean, I'm sorry.

07:43.713 --> 07:47.425
Am I the luckiest man in the world?
I don't even drink and I feel giddy drunk.

07:47.509 --> 07:50.011
My two most perfect students together.

07:50.887 --> 07:53.848
Oh, my goodness.
We gotta get this thing started.

07:54.432 --> 07:56.726
[sighs] I'm such a big fan.

07:57.394 --> 08:00.355
I know that sounds ridiculous,
but I've downloaded all of your music

08:00.438 --> 08:03.191
and that <i>New York Times</i> magazine profile
last month of you,

08:03.274 --> 08:05.944
those photos of you were amazing,
and the way--

08:06.486 --> 08:08.530
I was nine when I first saw you perform.

08:09.155 --> 08:11.825
You were 14 and everything I wanted to be.

08:12.283 --> 08:13.243
My idol.

08:13.785 --> 08:15.787
Please don`t be nervous
around me, Charlotte.

08:18.081 --> 08:19.916
I'm just so happy to finally meet you.

08:23.211 --> 08:24.212
[chuckles]

08:24.295 --> 08:25.672
[cello music plays]

08:51.197 --> 08:52.574
Wanna know a secret?

08:55.910 --> 08:57.662
The girl on the left is going to win.

08:57.746 --> 09:00.832
She's brilliant.
Leaves the other two in the dust.

09:03.835 --> 09:07.505
I agree, but that kind of takes
the drama out of it, doesn't it?

09:12.677 --> 09:13.887
You want drama?

09:16.848 --> 09:19.392
Watch that other girl's mother
in the blue dress.

09:22.645 --> 09:24.397
And the guy in the gray slacks.

09:25.190 --> 09:26.816
He's the father of the girl in the middle.

09:28.860 --> 09:30.695
There's something going on between them.

09:31.279 --> 09:32.864
They can't help themselves.

09:34.657 --> 09:37.285
[scoffs]
And right in front of their spouses.

09:38.244 --> 09:39.454
Just watch.

09:40.830 --> 09:42.957
I first noticed during semifinals.

09:44.375 --> 09:46.044
It's kind of hilarious.

09:48.129 --> 09:51.049
And... kind of hot.

09:54.052 --> 09:55.220
Just watch.

10:19.327 --> 10:20.370
Her hand...

10:42.058 --> 10:43.184
[sighs]

10:43.268 --> 10:45.520
I know I shouldn't spy, but...

10:47.605 --> 10:48.731
that...

10:51.067 --> 10:52.861
That gets me wet.

10:52.944 --> 10:53.987
[chuckles]

11:06.166 --> 11:08.835
[boat horn blares in distance]

11:29.189 --> 11:30.940
We've actually met once before.

11:32.692 --> 11:33.735
We have?

11:35.528 --> 11:38.281
It was the day you were leaving Bachoff.

11:39.699 --> 11:43.161
Your mom had just had her stroke,
and you had all your bags packed, and...

11:43.870 --> 11:49.167
I was just entering,
and I was nervous and excited, and...

11:50.168 --> 11:51.044
I saw you.

11:54.714 --> 11:55.757
My hero.

12:14.651 --> 12:15.652
[chuckles]

12:16.069 --> 12:17.570
That was a long time ago.

12:21.824 --> 12:23.243
Do you ever play anymore?

12:25.161 --> 12:27.580
It took me a while after I left Bachoff.

12:27.664 --> 12:29.916
Years to be honest, but now I...

12:30.458 --> 12:31.459
love it.

12:31.542 --> 12:33.670
-Because you're playing for yourself?
-Exactly.

12:33.753 --> 12:35.380
All that time with Anton,

12:36.631 --> 12:37.715
the practice,

12:38.424 --> 12:40.468
the performances,
the pressure to be perfect.

12:40.551 --> 12:42.095
-It was--
-I know.

12:42.845 --> 12:43.680
[chuckles]

12:45.974 --> 12:47.642
Do you ever think about leaving?

12:48.977 --> 12:50.061
Bachoff?

12:52.021 --> 12:54.399
It's my family. I can never.

12:55.942 --> 12:56.818
Never?

12:58.403 --> 12:59.570
No, never.

13:01.864 --> 13:04.450
And, anyway, the work.

13:05.159 --> 13:07.537
This special work.

13:08.746 --> 13:10.290
It's what's expected of us.

13:13.710 --> 13:15.044
I don't miss hearing that.

13:16.796 --> 13:20.341
Well, you'll be happy to know
I'm giving myself a little vacation.

13:20.425 --> 13:22.719
First one in forever. Starting tomorrow.

13:22.802 --> 13:24.053
-Amazing.
-I know.

13:24.512 --> 13:27.724
I know I can actually... sleep in.

13:27.807 --> 13:28.850
[both chuckle]

13:28.933 --> 13:32.687
Not dream about notes or scales,
rest my hands.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.106
Cause a little trouble.

13:35.898 --> 13:37.900
Have more than one drink in an evening.

13:38.693 --> 13:40.528
The baijiu is delicious.

13:41.529 --> 13:42.739
That is what I've heard.

13:43.948 --> 13:45.283
I better catch up.

13:55.251 --> 13:58.254
[both laugh]

13:58.338 --> 14:00.006
-[man grunts]
-[glass shatters]

14:04.052 --> 14:05.345
[speaking Mandarin]

14:07.430 --> 14:09.432
[grunting]

14:11.851 --> 14:13.519
Oh, Jesus!

14:13.603 --> 14:15.313
[speaking Mandarin]

14:23.488 --> 14:25.615
[man groans]

14:35.958 --> 14:37.960
[woman] Was it something he ate?

14:38.044 --> 14:40.129
I hope it isn't linked
to what's happening down south.

14:41.047 --> 14:42.507
What's happening down south?

14:45.301 --> 14:47.678
Some sort of hemorrhagic fever
near the Hunan border.

14:48.054 --> 14:50.181
Passed in the air.
Real contagion-like stuff.

14:54.519 --> 14:56.229
We were just scouting in Hunan.

14:56.312 --> 14:57.563
Oh, it can't be that.

14:57.647 --> 14:58.898
[scoffs] I sure hope not.

14:59.315 --> 15:02.068
You know how Anton likes to find his
protégés in remote places.

15:02.735 --> 15:05.613
-Hunan, Cambodia--
-Minnesota.

15:05.696 --> 15:06.781
Tampa.

15:07.949 --> 15:09.909
Will you go dancing with me later?

15:13.204 --> 15:14.163
Yes.

15:16.707 --> 15:17.750
Good.

15:17.834 --> 15:20.920
[Paloma] Lizzie, there you are.
Anton is asking for you.

15:21.629 --> 15:22.588
Come.

15:26.384 --> 15:27.844
[indistinct chatter]

15:30.555 --> 15:31.556
Elizabeth.

15:31.889 --> 15:34.142
Elizabeth. I was just telling
Geoffrey and Theis

15:34.225 --> 15:36.394
that I was hoping
that we could convince you to play

15:36.477 --> 15:39.480
one short piece, please.

15:40.398 --> 15:41.524
[exhales]

15:41.607 --> 15:45.194
Only if you can convince Charlotte
to play second cello with me.

15:46.154 --> 15:48.239
-My goodness. Yes, please.
-No.

15:48.322 --> 15:50.366
-No.
-No. no. no. We must.

15:50.450 --> 15:53.119
No. Lizzie, Lizzie. I couldn't.

15:53.202 --> 15:54.495
[Anton] Perfect. Please.

15:54.579 --> 15:56.372
Please! Yes, make it happen.

15:56.456 --> 15:58.583
-My goodness.
-Cello duet number three?

15:58.666 --> 15:59.876
[Anton] Oh, yes, perfect.

15:59.959 --> 16:02.336
-I know you still know it.
-[Theis] It's a dream come true.

16:02.420 --> 16:03.379
Lizzie...

16:04.380 --> 16:06.090
Lizzie, I'm an amateur now.

16:07.467 --> 16:10.094
You have been and always will be

16:10.178 --> 16:13.347
the person who makes 
my heart skip a beat when you play.

16:21.063 --> 16:23.274
Ladies and gentlemen.
Ladies and gentlemen.

16:23.941 --> 16:28.446
We are all about to witness
something extraordinary.

16:55.556 --> 16:57.099
[music plays]

19:12.693 --> 19:14.487
[moans]

19:15.738 --> 19:18.157
[moaning continues]

19:18.240 --> 19:19.617
[inaudible]

19:25.456 --> 19:26.499
[exhales]

19:38.594 --> 19:40.554
Have you ever been with a woman before?

19:42.306 --> 19:44.684
I've never been with anyone before.

19:47.269 --> 19:48.771
No one? Ever?

19:50.481 --> 19:52.900
My mom got sick, I went home.

19:53.901 --> 19:57.697
So, everything else just got put on hold.

20:01.033 --> 20:03.994
So, I'm your first.

20:04.078 --> 20:05.329
[chuckles]

20:05.830 --> 20:08.666
First and best.

20:08.749 --> 20:10.668
[laughs]

20:27.685 --> 20:29.478
I'm traveling out west tomorrow.

20:31.731 --> 20:32.815
Come with me.

20:34.066 --> 20:35.025
Really?

20:36.277 --> 20:37.236
Yeah.

20:38.279 --> 20:39.613
I'm doing it rough and tumble.

20:40.030 --> 20:42.158
Small buses, weird towns.

20:42.241 --> 20:44.827
As far away from first class as I can get.

20:45.786 --> 20:48.456
Unplugged from everything and everyone.

20:52.001 --> 20:53.627
I think we could have fun together.

20:54.962 --> 20:56.338
I think we could, too.

21:05.431 --> 21:07.767
I've never met anyone like you before.

21:10.853 --> 21:13.481
I mean, we're so different.

21:15.316 --> 21:16.400
And yet...

21:17.860 --> 21:19.737
we're more alike than it may seem.

21:26.869 --> 21:28.370
[inaudible]

21:34.585 --> 21:37.379
[pop music playing]

21:53.437 --> 21:54.522
[Charlotte] Good morning.

21:59.026 --> 22:01.278
[Lizzie] [groans] Good morning, you.

22:04.114 --> 22:05.032
[sighs]

22:05.115 --> 22:06.992
Are you as hungover as I am?

22:07.493 --> 22:08.786
Pretty much, yeah.

22:09.787 --> 22:12.540
I am out of practice
on the binge drinking.

22:13.582 --> 22:15.626
That Chinese vodka is brutal.

22:16.126 --> 22:17.211
Do you want some ibuprofen?

22:17.294 --> 22:19.296
Please. God, yes.

22:20.589 --> 22:22.049
[Lizzie]
My head is throbbing.

22:22.132 --> 22:23.717
I need like 50 of them.

22:28.597 --> 22:30.724
The pharmacy is open for business.

22:35.020 --> 22:36.689
What is that? Hair of the dog?

22:37.064 --> 22:38.399
It's the best cure.

22:39.358 --> 22:40.609
We're on vacation, right?

22:41.610 --> 22:43.404
[announcer speaking in Mandarin over PA]

22:51.120 --> 22:52.997
[Lizzie]
You really don't speak any Mandarin?

22:53.831 --> 22:55.457
Like, not even <i>ni hao?</i>

22:55.749 --> 22:58.377
I can say <i>ni hao, </i>but what you just did,

22:59.044 --> 23:00.170
buying bus tickets...

23:00.254 --> 23:02.089
I mean, that would have taken me
three hours

23:02.172 --> 23:06.093
and lots of manic hand gestures
and then desperate crying

23:06.176 --> 23:09.388
and then probably we would have
ended up in South Korea. [laughs]

23:10.222 --> 23:13.392
Or you could have just used a bus
and a ticket emoji. It's the same thing.

23:13.475 --> 23:15.519
Okay. Well, that is an excellent point.

23:16.937 --> 23:18.564
Are you sure you're okay?

23:19.064 --> 23:20.482
You look like you're struggling.

23:22.318 --> 23:23.777
Honestly, I feel like shit.

23:24.111 --> 23:25.988
Okay. Well, are you sure you want
to do this?

23:26.071 --> 23:29.033
We can just go back to the hotel
for the day and order pay-per-view

23:29.116 --> 23:30.659
and you can get your head right.

23:31.201 --> 23:32.661
No, I only have two weeks.

23:32.745 --> 23:34.413
I don't want to waste any of it.

23:37.583 --> 23:38.751
Play through the pain.

23:39.793 --> 23:41.003
Play through the pain.

23:41.086 --> 23:43.130
Don't you wanna get some food
before we leave?

23:43.213 --> 23:44.214
It might help.

23:45.382 --> 23:46.342
Okay.

23:52.264 --> 23:53.349
[grill sizzles]

24:02.149 --> 24:03.150
[groans]

24:13.410 --> 24:14.995
Worst idea in history?

24:15.788 --> 24:16.622
[chuckles]

24:18.040 --> 24:20.876
All I need is for my stomach
to go haywire on that bus.

24:20.960 --> 24:23.295
Should we just get the check
and pretend this never happened?

24:23.379 --> 24:24.672
This is your moment.

24:24.755 --> 24:27.508
You can bow out gracefully
and I'll never hold it against you.

24:28.342 --> 24:30.344
Just go to the airport like we never met?

24:30.427 --> 24:31.387
Exactly.

24:31.845 --> 24:34.807
Lizzie. Lizzie who?

24:34.890 --> 24:37.851
I have no idea who you're talking about.

24:37.935 --> 24:39.770
[laughs] Don't make me laugh.

24:41.939 --> 24:44.441
[announcer speaking Mandarin over PA]

24:47.611 --> 24:49.154
Are you sure you wanna do this?

24:49.571 --> 24:52.282
I'm fine. I just need to sit down.

25:03.127 --> 25:04.545
-Oh, God.
-What?

25:04.628 --> 25:06.755
-Nothing.
-What?

25:06.839 --> 25:08.966
-There was a bug.
-Jesus.

25:09.049 --> 25:11.927
Yeah, this bus hasn't been cleaned
since maybe ever.

25:12.011 --> 25:13.679
Well, I told you it was gonna be--

25:13.762 --> 25:15.931
Rough and tumble. You weren't kidding.

25:16.348 --> 25:17.683
[groans]

25:18.392 --> 25:21.145
There's like a fire in my head.
It's so crazy.

25:21.228 --> 25:22.229
Do you want some water?

25:22.646 --> 25:23.522
Yeah.

25:24.732 --> 25:25.566
Here you go.

25:41.790 --> 25:42.875
Oh, fuck.

25:43.333 --> 25:46.295
[exhales] It's like my mouth
has never been so fucking dry.

25:46.378 --> 25:47.713
[Lizzie sighs]

25:48.172 --> 25:49.590
I need another ibuprofen.

25:50.507 --> 25:51.592
Okay.

25:52.259 --> 25:54.470
I'll be better after a few of these,
I swear.

25:55.387 --> 25:56.305
Thank you.

25:56.972 --> 26:00.267
No, no, no. That's too many.
Is that a good idea on an empty stomach?

26:06.648 --> 26:07.649
[groans]

26:08.734 --> 26:09.693
[sighs]

26:11.528 --> 26:14.073
This is good. I'll be... I'll be good now.

26:14.656 --> 26:17.534
I'll be good. I'll be good.

26:19.036 --> 26:20.579
[bus engine starts]

26:20.662 --> 26:22.831
[honking]

26:49.441 --> 26:50.776
["Ready Or Not" plays]

26:50.859 --> 26:51.902
<i>♪ I get loud ♪</i>

26:51.985 --> 26:53.779
<i>♪ I ain't scared to say what I feel ♪</i>

26:53.862 --> 26:56.115
<i>♪ Add fuel to my fire</i>
<i>Or get out of my face ♪</i>

26:56.198 --> 26:58.784
<i>♪ I'm first, you're second</i>
<i>So stay in your place ♪</i>

26:58.867 --> 27:01.453
<i>♪ I go hard</i>
<i>Just to go harder again ♪</i>

27:01.537 --> 27:04.039
<i>♪ Push myself to the limit</i>
<i>To come back with the win ♪</i>

27:04.123 --> 27:06.750
<i>♪ Yeah, it's real in the field</i>
<i>When you rocking this ill ♪</i>

