44:09.480 --> 44:10.815
Spectacular, isn't it?

44:12.066 --> 44:14.819
Converted from a chapel
nearly a hundred years ago.

44:15.778 --> 44:18.781
Based on the Musikverein in Vienna.

44:19.615 --> 44:22.285
Zhang Li, come here. Come up here.

44:24.829 --> 44:25.955
Come on. Come.

44:27.165 --> 44:28.916
Okay, now stand right here.

44:29.000 --> 44:30.209
Right here.

44:30.293 --> 44:32.879
And I want you to sing a note.

44:33.254 --> 44:34.964
Hm. A sharp.

44:35.339 --> 44:36.215
Hm.

44:40.052 --> 44:40.887
Sing.

44:42.513 --> 44:44.765
[singing]

44:47.185 --> 44:48.853
Doesn't that sound incredible?

44:50.813 --> 44:53.107
I believe this to be the most...

44:53.774 --> 44:56.402
acoustically perfect room
I've ever been in.

44:56.485 --> 44:58.571
-[Zhang Li] It's beautiful.
-And...

44:58.654 --> 45:00.448
very few students

45:01.115 --> 45:03.075
are invited to play here.

45:03.159 --> 45:07.371
It takes years and years
of intense practice.

45:07.455 --> 45:08.664
But the best,

45:09.332 --> 45:10.541
the very best,

45:10.625 --> 45:12.043
Lizzie, for example,

45:12.501 --> 45:14.754
Charlotte Willmore, before her.

45:16.297 --> 45:18.299
If you are as exceptional

45:18.758 --> 45:22.720
as they are, and Zhang Li,
I believe you may be,

45:22.803 --> 45:26.182
well, then you can have the chance
to perform here

45:26.265 --> 45:28.517
and then you can have the chance...

45:29.852 --> 45:30.978
for greatness.

45:55.253 --> 45:56.295
[doorbell buzzes]

45:59.882 --> 46:01.550
[buzzing continues]

46:07.431 --> 46:08.391
Hello.

46:11.185 --> 46:12.937
[doorbell buzzes]

46:13.604 --> 46:15.022
Hello, who is it?

46:18.234 --> 46:19.277
[groans]

46:21.279 --> 46:22.613
Who is it, please?

46:24.365 --> 46:25.574
[clears throat] Hello.

46:28.953 --> 46:29.787
Who is it?

46:38.629 --> 46:39.505
Oh, my God.

46:40.631 --> 46:41.674
Where have you been?

46:42.675 --> 46:45.386
What's... What's happened to you?
We've been looking for you.

46:47.430 --> 46:48.472
Elizabeth.

46:51.767 --> 46:53.019
What happened to your hand?

46:59.400 --> 47:01.444
[shouts]
What the hell happened to your hand?

47:03.029 --> 47:05.197
They found me on the side of a mountain.

47:06.615 --> 47:08.034
Drugged out of my mind.

47:09.660 --> 47:10.995
Covered in blood.

47:12.997 --> 47:16.167
With nothing but a homemade tourniquet
keeping me alive.

47:18.878 --> 47:20.838
The police tried to help me, but...

47:22.715 --> 47:24.967
I'm the one who took the pills.

47:25.843 --> 47:27.094
I'm the one who...

47:27.803 --> 47:29.388
chopped my own hand off.

47:31.474 --> 47:33.476
Once I woke up in the hospital, and...

47:34.310 --> 47:38.105
once the drugs were out of my system,
and I could think clearly again...

47:40.191 --> 47:42.109
Charlotte was already out of the country.

47:42.193 --> 47:44.070
I still can't understand.

47:44.153 --> 47:46.155
Why? Why would she do this?

47:47.031 --> 47:48.074
Because...

47:49.158 --> 47:51.702
Because she's a jealous fucking bitch!

47:53.412 --> 47:54.413
I had...

47:54.997 --> 47:57.583
music, fame...

47:58.793 --> 47:59.794
you.

48:00.836 --> 48:02.129
And she couldn't stand that.

48:02.213 --> 48:04.673
She couldn't stand
that I replaced her. She...

48:05.174 --> 48:08.427
tracked me down to China, befriended me,

48:08.969 --> 48:11.389
slept with me, poisoned me.

48:11.472 --> 48:15.184
All that because I had the life
that she so desperately wanted.

48:15.267 --> 48:16.852
My God. God.

48:17.770 --> 48:19.730
[cries]
And now it's gone. It is...

48:19.814 --> 48:21.941
It is completely gone.

48:22.817 --> 48:23.943
Elizabeth, it's...

48:24.235 --> 48:25.694
It's going to be okay.

48:25.778 --> 48:27.863
She took everything from me.

48:29.281 --> 48:30.533
Everything!

48:42.795 --> 48:44.547
[clock ticking]

48:46.715 --> 48:47.758
[screams]

48:50.803 --> 48:51.762
[screams]

48:56.809 --> 48:57.810
[sniffles]

49:00.771 --> 49:01.939
[screams]

49:08.904 --> 49:10.656
[cello playing]

49:20.583 --> 49:21.625
[Anton] More tension.

49:22.877 --> 49:23.794
Yes.

49:25.504 --> 49:27.089
Good. Good.

49:27.173 --> 49:29.175
Play through the pain. Good.

49:37.766 --> 49:38.684
Right.

49:39.602 --> 49:40.478
Don't...

49:53.032 --> 49:55.910
Actually, Elizabeth,
when practice is over,

49:55.993 --> 49:57.786
do you have a minute to talk?

50:01.081 --> 50:02.208
[door closes]

50:04.001 --> 50:05.461
I don't understand.

50:07.671 --> 50:08.756
You're kicking me out?

50:10.341 --> 50:11.717
I have nowhere to go.

50:11.800 --> 50:13.177
We found you a place.

50:13.636 --> 50:16.055
By the museum,
right next to Central Avenue T Station.

50:16.138 --> 50:17.139
We'll pay for it.

50:17.223 --> 50:19.391
Pay for all of it.
Pay for your rehabilitation.

50:19.475 --> 50:22.353
But I can still be useful, Anton.
I can teach.

50:23.562 --> 50:25.606
Music is my life.

50:25.689 --> 50:26.690
Look at us.

50:27.566 --> 50:28.776
You know what this is.

50:29.652 --> 50:31.028
How we work here.

50:31.111 --> 50:32.696
We have Theis and Geoffrey.

50:32.780 --> 50:34.698
We don't need any more teachers.

50:34.782 --> 50:37.076
But I can conduct, and I can compose.

50:37.159 --> 50:38.285
Fuck, I'll scrub the toilets!

50:38.369 --> 50:40.454
Just don't... Don't shut me out.

50:42.081 --> 50:43.374
[sobs] Please.

50:44.250 --> 50:45.251
Anton...

50:46.418 --> 50:47.753
if you accept me,

50:47.836 --> 50:49.797
the music world will accept me.

50:50.589 --> 50:52.132
Don't you understand that?

50:52.758 --> 50:54.885
You have that power.

50:54.969 --> 50:56.762
You have that reputation.

50:57.137 --> 50:59.223
Your word means so much,

50:59.932 --> 51:01.642
but if you shut me out...

51:02.268 --> 51:04.228
[sobs] Please.

51:06.230 --> 51:07.314
Please.

51:08.774 --> 51:10.234
Don't be this person.

51:11.443 --> 51:13.028
Do not discard me.

51:13.112 --> 51:16.574
Lizzie, this is a music conservatory,
not a convalescent home.

51:20.286 --> 51:21.287
I'm sorry.

51:22.496 --> 51:23.872
I didn't mean it like that,

51:23.956 --> 51:26.584
but there are other girls
that we need to house and train.

51:30.296 --> 51:31.380
Anton...

51:33.632 --> 51:34.675
Please. [sobs]

51:37.052 --> 51:38.679
I don't know anything else.

51:40.889 --> 51:42.057
You had a gift.

51:44.059 --> 51:45.394
A rare and...

51:46.687 --> 51:49.273
beautiful talent like no other.

51:51.734 --> 51:53.360
But sadly, that gift is gone.

51:56.697 --> 51:58.073
I'm so sorry, Elizabeth.

52:03.495 --> 52:04.580
[softly] Please.

52:07.207 --> 52:09.460
[sighs]

52:25.643 --> 52:26.810
[sobs]

53:20.781 --> 53:21.990
[dog barking in the distance]

53:31.625 --> 53:32.668
[thuds]

53:37.005 --> 53:38.549
[bottle clanking]

53:54.857 --> 53:55.941
[door creaks]

54:07.411 --> 54:08.454
Hello?

54:41.695 --> 54:42.988
[electrical crackling]

54:44.615 --> 54:45.783
[grunts]

54:50.078 --> 54:51.205
[grunts]

54:51.288 --> 54:53.916
Fuck you. Crazy bitch!

54:53.999 --> 54:56.752
Fuck you! Fuck you!

54:56.835 --> 54:59.546
Fuck you. You fucking bitch!

55:08.931 --> 55:10.682
[breathes heavily]

55:13.101 --> 55:14.770
[operatic music playing]

55:31.078 --> 55:32.079
[Paloma] Anton.

55:34.957 --> 55:35.999
What's going on?

55:42.005 --> 55:42.923
Anton.

55:43.006 --> 55:43.966
Stay here.

55:48.554 --> 55:49.471
Lizzie.

55:51.223 --> 55:52.474
What are you doing here?

55:53.058 --> 55:54.726
You're gonna freeze to death.

55:57.604 --> 56:01.441
Look, I know this is hard,
but I thought I made myself clear.

56:01.525 --> 56:02.985
You just can't be here.

56:03.652 --> 56:05.362
Because I had nothing you wanted.

56:06.572 --> 56:07.656
Now I do.

56:08.574 --> 56:09.867
What are you talking about?

56:11.535 --> 56:12.661
What do you have?

56:14.037 --> 56:16.790
I have the bitch.

56:19.334 --> 56:20.502
Oh, my God.

56:22.588 --> 56:24.047
Lizzie, what have you done?

56:25.173 --> 56:26.091
Where is she?

56:28.594 --> 56:29.803
Where is she?

56:32.347 --> 56:34.683
In the trunk of my fucking car.

56:41.523 --> 56:42.733
So I can come home?

56:55.787 --> 56:56.663
Where is she?

56:57.623 --> 57:00.042
She's with Paloma, but don't worry.

57:00.125 --> 57:02.419
She... She can't hurt you.

57:02.502 --> 57:03.837
But she's crazy.

57:04.421 --> 57:06.006
She kidnapped me, Anton.

57:06.089 --> 57:08.050
I know. She's not well. Clearly.

57:09.635 --> 57:10.761
But frankly,

57:11.803 --> 57:12.971
neither are you.

57:15.307 --> 57:17.100
Were you really that jealous?

57:18.226 --> 57:19.478
I wasn't jealous.

57:21.521 --> 57:22.564
I was trying to help her.

57:24.316 --> 57:25.734
By cutting off her hand?

57:29.321 --> 57:31.531
I saw her picture in a magazine.

57:32.074 --> 57:33.700
I saw the tattoo on her back.

57:34.826 --> 57:35.911
The same as mine.

57:38.372 --> 57:39.623
I knew how she got it.

57:41.083 --> 57:44.044
I knew what she had to do to get it.

57:45.504 --> 57:47.965
And I knew she was brainwashed
just like I was

57:48.048 --> 57:50.926
until my mom got sick
and I had to go home.

57:52.844 --> 57:56.556
<i>I sat in that room with my mother</i>
<i>for a decade, slowly going crazy.</i>

57:57.015 --> 57:59.142
<i>I blamed myself for everything.</i>

57:59.226 --> 58:03.730
<i>I spent years in and out of</i>
<i>mental hospitals until, finally,</i>

58:03.814 --> 58:05.899
<i>with some help, I saw the light.</i>

58:07.484 --> 58:09.528
So I reached out...

58:11.196 --> 58:12.823
and came back into your lives.

58:16.660 --> 58:17.744
Came back why?

58:21.415 --> 58:23.041
Came back why, Charlotte?

58:23.125 --> 58:24.751
To help save her.

58:24.835 --> 58:26.753
Save her from what?

58:29.047 --> 58:30.048
From you.

58:33.635 --> 58:34.928
[stammers]

58:38.974 --> 58:40.434
[stammers and laughs]

58:44.062 --> 58:45.439
[laughs]

58:54.740 --> 58:56.283
[sighs deeply]

59:03.999 --> 59:05.709
[cello playing]

59:07.836 --> 59:09.046
[Anton] Very good.

59:12.132 --> 59:13.091
Very good.

59:14.426 --> 59:15.677
Back straight now.

59:17.804 --> 59:18.805
Excellent.

59:20.182 --> 59:21.767
More tension in the strings.

59:24.061 --> 59:26.271
Feel it happening inside of you,
Charlotte.

59:28.482 --> 59:29.441
Mm-hmm.

59:29.816 --> 59:30.776
Yes.

59:31.777 --> 59:32.694
Good.

59:43.288 --> 59:44.498
I made a mistake.

59:44.581 --> 59:45.582
Yes, you did.

59:47.459 --> 59:48.835
I'm sorry.

59:48.919 --> 59:50.420
And after all this time.

59:50.504 --> 59:52.172
-Forgive me.
-After all this training.

59:52.255 --> 59:53.465
Forgive me, Anton.

59:53.548 --> 59:55.926
After a promise for Carnegie Hall.

59:59.596 --> 1:00:01.890
[groans] Stop. Stop the crying.

1:00:02.390 --> 1:00:04.351
[sobs]

1:00:04.434 --> 1:00:05.644
Ouch.

1:00:06.311 --> 1:00:08.355
[yells] Stop the fucking crying!

1:00:08.814 --> 1:00:10.148
It won't happen again.

1:00:10.232 --> 1:00:12.275
In this room, it had better not.

1:00:12.359 --> 1:00:13.485
Never in this room.

1:00:13.568 --> 1:00:15.070
Because you know what happens next.

1:00:15.445 --> 1:00:16.780
-Yes, I do.
-Do you?

1:00:17.155 --> 1:00:18.115
Yes.

1:00:18.198 --> 1:00:19.950
[footsteps approach]

1:00:22.911 --> 1:00:24.788
We don't make mistakes here.

1:00:27.124 --> 1:00:29.209
Not when we represent the Academy.

1:00:39.219 --> 1:00:40.679
Whose name is on that gate?

1:00:41.721 --> 1:00:43.765
-Yours.
-Yes.

1:00:44.432 --> 1:00:47.227
Mine, my father's, grandfather's.

1:00:47.894 --> 1:00:49.187
This school is my blood.

1:00:49.729 --> 1:00:50.856
It's my history.

1:00:51.898 --> 1:00:55.485
I teach you the way they taught me,
the way they taught Theis and Geoffrey,

1:00:55.569 --> 1:00:59.614
and anyone who's fortunate enough
to earn their place here.

1:01:00.365 --> 1:01:01.741
But I can only take you so far.

1:01:01.825 --> 1:01:02.951
I will work harder.

1:01:03.034 --> 1:01:05.996
Oh, you will work harder.

1:01:07.372 --> 1:01:09.499
Why do we work so hard, Charlotte?

1:01:10.667 --> 1:01:11.626
To be the best.

1:01:11.710 --> 1:01:13.253
And why is that, Charlotte?

1:01:16.089 --> 1:01:18.008
Because it's what's expected of us.

1:01:24.806 --> 1:01:27.100
You got that tattoo because

1:01:27.184 --> 1:01:31.813
you were ready to play in this Chapel.

1:01:31.897 --> 1:01:34.274
You got that tattoo...

1:01:35.025 --> 1:01:36.651
because you were the very best.

1:01:37.527 --> 1:01:38.486
Yes, I know.

1:01:38.570 --> 1:01:40.197
And If you're not the very best,

1:01:40.989 --> 1:01:42.324
if you insult me...

1:01:42.949 --> 1:01:45.744
and Theis and Geoffrey with your mistakes?

1:01:46.578 --> 1:01:48.246
I discredit the Academy.

1:01:49.915 --> 1:01:50.832
Why?

1:01:52.334 --> 1:01:56.087
Because I was prepared for
The Perfection and failed.

1:01:57.214 --> 1:02:02.344
Prepared by our sweat,
passion, and reputation.

1:02:02.844 --> 1:02:06.139
Prepared by our sweat and passion
and reputation.

1:02:06.223 --> 1:02:08.350
Month after month, year after year.

1:02:10.644 --> 1:02:12.896
Month after month, year after year.

1:02:12.979 --> 1:02:14.522
[Anton]
Until you were ready.

1:02:17.150 --> 1:02:18.276
Until I was ready.

1:02:40.590 --> 1:02:41.675
[Anton] You failed.

1:02:42.425 --> 1:02:43.468
You failed.

1:02:47.055 --> 1:02:48.431
So what does that mean?

1:02:49.975 --> 1:02:51.685
What does that mean, Charlotte?

1:02:52.852 --> 1:02:55.855
When you fail
at the things that we teach you?

1:02:57.524 --> 1:02:59.025
I cannot get close to God.

1:02:59.109 --> 1:03:01.027
No, you cannot.

1:03:01.486 --> 1:03:03.488
And your talent will lay in waste.

1:03:03.989 --> 1:03:06.408
Squandered by your lack of ambition.

1:03:07.450 --> 1:03:08.743
So what happens now?

1:03:09.369 --> 1:03:11.288
-Now?
-Yes, what happens now?

1:03:11.371 --> 1:03:14.165
What happened to me,
what happened to Theis and Geoffrey?

1:03:14.249 --> 1:03:18.128
And every one of the chosen who failed?

1:03:22.882 --> 1:03:24.217
We pay the price.

1:03:32.475 --> 1:03:33.852
You pay the price.

1:03:35.520 --> 1:03:37.147
[muffled screaming]

1:03:38.606 --> 1:03:39.941
[sobbing]

1:03:42.110 --> 1:03:43.653
[grunting]

1:03:58.501 --> 1:03:59.544
[Anton grunts]

1:04:00.462 --> 1:04:01.504
[grunts]

1:04:03.757 --> 1:04:04.716
[grunts]

1:04:42.754 --> 1:04:46.049
Tonight, Charlotte, after so many years,

1:04:46.508 --> 1:04:48.593
you shall play for us again.

1:04:50.887 --> 1:04:51.888
I can't.

1:04:53.348 --> 1:04:56.017
-I'm not ready.
-Sonata for solo cello.

1:04:56.101 --> 1:04:58.228
I'm not ready to play here, Anton.

1:04:58.812 --> 1:04:59.979
Please.

1:05:00.063 --> 1:05:03.650
Well, here is where you must play.
Where you've always played.

1:05:04.567 --> 1:05:06.069
Theis, Geoffrey.

1:05:06.152 --> 1:05:06.986
No.

1:05:14.744 --> 1:05:16.371
And, of course, Paloma.

1:05:19.457 --> 1:05:20.291
Please.

1:05:20.708 --> 1:05:23.211
Paloma, you can stop this.

1:05:23.962 --> 1:05:24.963
Please.

1:05:25.547 --> 1:05:27.340
We do what we need to do, Charlotte.

1:05:28.508 --> 1:05:30.009
It's what's expected of us.

1:05:32.846 --> 1:05:36.015
Paloma's always adored
when you played perfectly. Well..

1:05:36.433 --> 1:05:37.475
we all did.

1:05:38.101 --> 1:05:40.019
That was always the goal.

1:05:40.103 --> 1:05:41.104
Right, Charlotte?

1:05:42.355 --> 1:05:43.481
The Perfection.

1:05:44.524 --> 1:05:47.652
This doesn't have to be like this, Anton.

1:05:51.698 --> 1:05:53.450
You really hate me, don't you?

1:05:54.909 --> 1:05:55.827
You...

1:05:55.910 --> 1:06:00.039
you hate me,
when all I ever did was believe in you.

1:06:00.123 --> 1:06:02.542
You know what you did to me.

1:06:02.625 --> 1:06:05.003
And you know it helped you become

1:06:05.503 --> 1:06:07.130
the rare talent that you were.

1:06:07.213 --> 1:06:08.923
I was a child.

1:06:09.674 --> 1:06:11.843
Lizzie was a child. We were children.

1:06:11.926 --> 1:06:14.637
You were students who achieved greatness.

1:06:15.430 --> 1:06:17.348
Just as my grandfather envisioned.

1:06:17.432 --> 1:06:19.684
Just like my father taught me.

1:06:20.518 --> 1:06:23.354
Everybody should be so lucky.

1:06:24.814 --> 1:06:25.690
Lizzie.

1:06:26.816 --> 1:06:28.151
Were you abused?

1:06:29.110 --> 1:06:31.696
Is that what you would call it,
what we did for you?

1:06:38.495 --> 1:06:39.954
To play that music,

1:06:41.372 --> 1:06:43.291
to achieve The Perfection...

1:06:48.087 --> 1:06:49.380
it was a gift.

1:06:55.220 --> 1:06:56.387
You see, Charlotte?

1:06:57.555 --> 1:06:59.599
You cut off her hand for nothing.

1:07:01.226 --> 1:07:02.435
Lizzie, if you would.

1:07:07.232 --> 1:07:08.399
Well, you must remember our...

1:07:09.192 --> 1:07:12.278
little rituals. The drinks, the formality.

1:07:14.030 --> 1:07:15.156
Consequences.

1:07:17.492 --> 1:07:19.160
Oh, but you were just a child then.

1:07:20.620 --> 1:07:22.622
Most things really have not changed.

1:07:22.705 --> 1:07:24.374
Well, actually...

1:07:25.542 --> 1:07:27.085
there is one thing that has changed.

1:07:29.712 --> 1:07:31.381
If you achieve The Perfection,

1:07:31.464 --> 1:07:34.968
which is what's expected
of you this evening, then...

1:07:36.719 --> 1:07:37.971
you can go.

1:07:39.931 --> 1:07:41.933
I'm a taskmaster, yes, but...

1:07:42.892 --> 1:07:44.644
I'm not a monster. [chuckles]

1:07:47.063 --> 1:07:48.606
But if you should make a mistake,

1:07:49.566 --> 1:07:51.609
if you miss one minor note...

1:07:53.903 --> 1:07:55.822
well, it won't be you who pays the price.

1:07:57.073 --> 1:07:58.908
Paloma, if you would.

1:08:03.788 --> 1:08:05.873
We're ready for you, sweetheart. Come.

1:08:06.499 --> 1:08:07.417
[Anton] Ah.

1:08:08.126 --> 1:08:12.714
